---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const baseUrl = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.endsWith('/')
  ? import.meta.env.BASE_URL
  : `${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/`;
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Quickstart"
  description="Get started with CodeArmy: prerequisites, first steps, and the Alice/CodeArmy relationship."
>
  <section class="container page-hero">
    <p class="eyebrow">Quickstart</p>
    <h1>From zero to first campaign in 30 minutes.</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      CodeArmy turns long-horizon coding and research into structured, repo-first campaigns. 
      This guide covers prerequisites, the Alice/CodeArmy split, and your first concrete steps.
    </p>
    <div class="hero-actions">
      <a class="button" href="https://github.com/Alice-space/alice">
        Clone Alice Runtime
      </a>
      <a class="button-secondary" href={`${baseUrl}how-it-works/`}>
        Read How It Works
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container page-body">
    <div class="split-grid">
      <div>
        <h2>Prerequisites</h2>
        <p class="section-copy">
          Before starting, ensure you have the following set up:
        </p>
        <ul class="page-list">
          <li><strong>Git</strong> — Version 2.30 or later</li>
          <li><strong>GitHub account</strong> — For campaign repos and collaboration</li>
          <li><strong>Trae Solo</strong> — Recommended editor with agent support (VS Code with extensions also works)</li>
          <li><strong>Node.js 18+</strong> — Required if using CLI tools and local site preview</li>
        </ul>
        <div class="callout" style="margin-top: 1rem;">
          <strong>Not sure about Trae?</strong>
          Trae Solo is the primary interface for CodeArmy campaigns. It provides agent loops, 
          MCP tool integration, and Skills support. Download from 
          <a href="https://trae.ai" target="_blank" rel="noopener">trae.ai</a>.
        </div>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2>Alice and CodeArmy: The split</h2>
        <p class="section-copy">
          Understanding the relationship between these two names is key to using the system correctly.
        </p>
        <ul class="page-list">
          <li>
            <strong>Alice</strong> — The underlying runtime and orchestration engine. 
            This is where the code lives and executes.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>CodeArmy</strong> — The product layer: workflows, conventions, and interfaces 
            built on top of Alice. This is what you interact with.
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p class="section-copy">
          Think of it as: <em>Alice runs the engine; CodeArmy provides the playbook.</em>
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="split-grid" style="margin-top: 2rem;">
      <div>
        <h2>First steps</h2>
        <ol class="page-list">
          <li>
            <strong>Clone the Alice runtime repo</strong>
            <pre style="background: rgba(19,34,56,0.06); padding: 0.75rem 1rem; border-radius: 0.5rem; margin-top: 0.5rem; overflow-x: auto;"><code>git clone https://github.com/Alice-space/alice.git
cd alice</code></pre>
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Set up your campaign structure</strong> — Create a campaign repo following the 
            <a href={`${baseUrl}how-it-works/`}>How It Works</a> conventions.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Initialize your first campaign</strong> — Define objective, baseline, and gates 
            in <code>campaign.md</code>.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Run your first reconcile</strong> — Check campaign state and generate initial task packages.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Execute a task</strong> — Pick a bounded task, dispatch to an executor, and review output.
          </li>
        </ol>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2>What this page covers (and doesn't)</h2>
        <p class="section-copy">
          This quickstart is designed to get you oriented and moving. It does not cover:
        </p>
        <ul class="page-list">
          <li>
            <strong>Not covered:</strong> Detailed planner/reviewer/executor workflows — 
            see <a href={`${baseUrl}how-it-works/`}>How It Works</a>
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Not covered:</strong> Integration specifics for Feishu, Slack, or custom channels — 
            see <a href={`${baseUrl}integrations/`}>Integrations</a>
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Not covered:</strong> Research case studies and advanced patterns — 
            see <a href={`${baseUrl}research-use-cases/`}>Research Use Cases</a>
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Not covered:</strong> Roadmap and upcoming features — 
            see <a href={`${baseUrl}roadmap/`}>Roadmap</a>
          </li>
        </ul>
        <div class="callout" style="margin-top: 1rem;">
          <strong>Stuck?</strong>
          The <a href={`${baseUrl}how-it-works/`}>How It Works</a> page explains the 
          campaign model in detail. For implementation questions, check the 
          <a href="https://github.com/Alice-space/alice">Alice repo</a> issues and discussions.
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="callout" style="margin-top: 2rem;">
      <strong>Next steps after Quickstart</strong>
      <div class="hero-actions" style="margin-top: 1rem;">
        <a class="button" href={`${baseUrl}how-it-works/`}>Understand the Model</a>
        <a class="button-secondary" href={`${baseUrl}integrations/`}>Choose Integration</a>
        <a class="button-secondary" href={`${baseUrl}research-use-cases/`}>See Use Cases</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
